About Us | Price's Wood Products Home About About Us About Cypress Products Cypress Products Hardwood Products Tongue & Groove Beams Flooring Kiln Services Moulding Our Location Contact Us Select Page About Price’s Wood Products About Price’s Wood Products exceptional team. Here at Price’s Wood Products, we are the Alpha and the Omega, your lumber starts with us from the growing timber and ends in a finished product with unmatched quality.  Our management team has over 125 years of combined experience in the wood products industry. We are not resellers of other companies products; we are a professional manufacturer of custom lumber products. Our team knows the lumber grade rules, knows the capability of our products, and adheres to our motto of delivering only the best wood products in the industry. We tailor to our customers’ specific needs with attention to the details. We have a state of the art operation that allows us to be efficient and precise in our manufacture of your product. We have the ability to Saw, Kiln, Dry, Profile, Store, and Package our full range of lumber products. This allows us to maintain tight tolerances, exceptional Q/C, and the high standards our customers have come to expect. Price’s Wood Products Owner’s Message “I believe in building strong relationships with our customers. I have instilled this in our team, because a satisfied customer will be back to purchase our products again. I invite you to explore our website, learn about the details of our processes, products, and how we can help YOU our customer succeed in your endeavors. Please reach out to us so we can assist with your next project.” Our owner has over 20 years in the timber procurement, sawmilling, kiln drying, and final manufacturing stages of Cypress lumber and southern hardwoods. Because of this PWP is nationally recognized as an expert in these fields. We are a privately owned company dedicated to providing customer satisfaction and top of the line lumber and millwork products. Who we are Retail sales – Nationwide DIY , Home Owners, Contractors, and Architects. Wholesale – Nationwide and Export Customers in truckload quantities from small private lumber yards to massive public distribution yards. Who we service Retail customers – via internet nationwide and locally. Homeowners, Builders, Contractors, Architects and D-I-Y’s. Wholesale customers – nationwide. To Buy From Us Contact us by phone or email Use the “Contact Us’ for to send details of your needs What We Do Produce and ship Cypress Products nationwide. Produce flooring and mouldings from almost any species of wood. Sell a variety of wood products. Custom Kiln Dry Lumber for commercial and wholesale customers. Manufacturing Capabilities Our modern machinery empowers us to produce high-quality millwork products, including Cypress tongue and groove, siding, and various types of moulding. Our slogan, “Where are the knife marks?” reflects our commitment to delivering exceptionally smooth products. Our facility includes three dry kilns with a total capacity of 190,000 board feet, an automatic lumber stacker, and a Newman 382 quiet cut 30″ double surface planer. We also have a Weinig 23C Hydromat moulder, straight line rip saws, gang rip saws, band resaw, and double end trimming equipment. Our lumber inspection process ensures quality at every stage of production, along with efficient container unloading and loading. We boast a 1,000,000 BF dry storage capacity and truck scales. With our extensive equipment and milling expertise, we can produce just about anything you need. Contact us today to discuss your specific requirements Payment Types Contact Us  Phone (225) 718 – 4297 (225) 718 – 4296  Address 12100 LA-77, Maringouin, LA 70757  Email sales@cypresswood.net Privacy Policy Terms of Use Cajun Cloud Services LLC | © Copyright 2025

Student-Athlete PPE More Staff Directory Nicolette Marinello, MS ATC Head Athletic Trainer Nicolette Marinello was selected for the Athletic Trainer position in Fall 2021 after serving as an hourly athletic trainer with Cypress College since 2019. Nicolette has had a diverse background in the field of athletic training thus far. Nicolette received her Bachelor’s degree in Kinesiology with an emphasis in Athletic Training from Chapman University. She had the opportunity to work with Chapman’s athletic teams on the field and in the clinic during athletic games and practices. She graduated with her Master’s Degree in Athletic Training from Chapman University and provided care at multiple colleges including Vanguard University, Chapman University, Cypress College, El Camino College, and Mt. SAC Community College. Through those experiences, she learned to work with collegiate athletes from many different sports including football, soccer, lacrosse, softball, baseball, tennis, water polo, volleyball, and basketball. Prior to the COVID-19 pandemic, Nicolette provided care to athletes from Cypress College and LA Galaxy through rehabilitating injured athletes and assisting in injury prevention protocols with her fellow sports performance specialists. While working with LA Galaxy, she gained experience in treating injuries in elite athletes at the highest level of competition as well as closely collaborating with the registered dieticians and strength and conditioning specialists. Nicolette had been working at Cypress College as a part-time Athletic Trainer since summer of 2019 and had taken the full-time Athletic Trainer position starting in Fall of 2021. She continues to strive for the best comprehensive wellness approach for all student-athletes by encompassing a larger health care team, including Team Physician, Team Fellows, Team Physical Therapist, Team Chiropractor, Sports Psychologist, Dietician, and Team Dentist. As the Head Athletic Trainer, Nicolette oversees all medical aspects of the 14 intercollegiate sport programs. Nicolette believes that treating the patient as a whole is the optimal approach to comprehensive wellness. She believes wellness encompasses mental and socioemotional wellbeing in addition to physical health. She continues to improve the student-athlete experience by building a health care team to allow for the highest level of student success. Athletic training is an ever-evolving field, and she strives to be progressive in her practice. In a field of continuous new advancements and innovations in health care, she believes it is essential to embrace lifelong learning and integrate emerging evidence-based practice to enhance patient care. Athletic Training Clinic: (714)-484-7381 (office) Email: nmarinello@cypresscollege.edu Rachael Kirkpatrick, DAT, ATC Head Athletic Trainer Rachael Kirkpatrick join ed the Charger family in Fall of 2021 as Head Athletic Trainer. She comes to us from Barstow College where she served as the Head Athletic Trainer for 5 years. Rachael began her education at Chapman University. In 2014, she earned a Bachelor of Science in Athletic Training with a Minor in Psychology. During her undergraduate time, Rachael completed clinical rotations at 2 fellow CCCAA institutions, local Orange County Public and Private High Schools, USA Volleyball and volunteered with the Anaheim Ducks of the NHL. After graduating from Chapman, Rachael continued her education at Indiana State University where she earned a Doctorate in Athletic Training (DAT) in May of 2017. During her time as a Graduate Assistant Athletic Trainer, Rachael served as the Head Athletic Trainer for North Vermillion High School in Cayuga, IN. In 2017, Rachael returned to California and became the Head Athletic Trainer at Barstow College from 2017-2021. With the Vikings, Rachael also served in dual roles as the Interim Athletic Director (‘18-’20) and Eligibility Specialist (‘20-’21). Additionally, Rachael supported the following programs while at BCC: Food Insecurity Committee Student Engagement Committee Chaired the Community “B Well” Health and Wellness Fair 2017, 2018 1 st Annual Student PRIDE Celebration Authored the BCC COVID-19 Athletics Return Plan CCCATA COVID-19 Advisory Committee In Fall of 2021, Rachael Kirkpatrick and Nicolette Marinello, took over as Co-Head Athletic Trainers for Cypress College Athletics. Cypress College Sports Medicine strives to provide holistic patient-centered care with its diverse healthcare team. Since 2022, Kirkpatrick and Marinello have developed a comprehensive medical staff including: Team Sports Medicine Physicians, Orthopedic Surgeons, Physical Therapist, Sports Medicine Chiropractor, Sport Psychologist, Dietitian, and Dentist. It is the mission of Cypress College Sports Medicine to provide 1) evidence-based care, 2) personalized accessible interventions, and 3) an inclusive environment. Rachael currently serves as an institution representative within the Orange Empire Conference (OEC) as well as a member of the Student-Athlete Advisory Committee (SAAC). Rachael volunteers as a Clinical Preceptor for both CSULB and CSUF Master of Science in Athletic Training (MSAT) students. She is passionate about Athletic Training and believes in the importance of mentoring and developing the next generation of healthcare providers. Rachael looks forward to continuing to develop and advance the Sports Medicine Department at Cypress College. Go Chargers! Athletic Training Clinic: (714)-484-7381 (office) Email: rkirkpatrick@cypresscollege.edu Ellexis Khan, M.D. Team Physician Ellexis Khan, MD, attended medical school at Ross University in Dominica, and went on to complete her residency in family medicine at Robert Wood Johnson University Hospital in New Brunswick, New Jersey. After her residency, she completed her fellowship in primary care sports medicine at UC Irvine. She chose a career in primary care sports medicine because of her passion for athletics. After playing Rugby during her undergraduate at BYU, she knew she wanted to stay connected with sports and athletes by providing a service needed for athletes at any age. Dr. Khan enjoys working with patients to provide options to help make informed decisions with their health care. MemorialCare Medical Group – Long Beach (Sports Medicine) https://www.memorialcare.org/services/sports-medicine Joshua Snodgrass, M.D., CAQSM Team Physician Joshua Snodgrass, MD, is thrilled to be coming onboard as a MemorialCare Medical Group physician. As both a Primary Care and Sports Medicine provider, Dr. Snodgrass is dedicated to caring for his patients as a whole and is active in discovering emerging technologies and treatments, including sports concussion and evaluation experience with ultrasound-guided musculoskeletal injections. He is also Titleist Performance Institute Certified, which is the world's leading educational organization dedicated to the study of how the human body functions in relation to the golf swing. Dr. Snodgrass has a variety of Sports Medicine affiliations, including holding a position as Team Physician for Long Beach State Athletics and Cypress College.
